Jefferies Names Sean Huang to Head Securities Finance Asia

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-05-24T13:47:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/jefferies-names-sean-huang-to-head-securities-finance-asia-1-.html
Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF) , the investment
bank that has been expanding since the financial crisis, hired
Sean Huang to head securities finance trading in Asia,  Huang was a senior trader in equity finance at  UBS AG (UBSN) , New
York-based Jefferies said today in a statement. He will be based
in Hong Kong, according to the statement.  Huang’s hiring is part of Jefferies’s strategy to build its
equity sales, trading and research businesses in Asia. Last
month, the firm said it added six managing directors in the
region, including Stephen Nichols, head of Asia trading from
Citigroup Inc., and Adam Putterill, head of Hong Kong and China
sales trading, from  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)   “Our equity platform continues to gain market share as we
focus on delivering new products and services to our
institutional client base globally,” Mike Alexander, chief
executive officer of Jefferies Asia, said in the statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Laura Marcinek in  New York  at 
 lmarcinek3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scheer at 
 dscheer@bloomberg.net . 